Needless to say, that‚Äôs a lot to worry about with uploads in conjunction with background `URLSession`. If you‚Äôre uploading huge assets (e.g. videos) over slow connections, perhaps you need that. But the other (simpler) alternative is to use a default `URLSession` configuration, and just tell the OS that even if the user leaves your app, request a few more minutes to finish the upload. Just use standard completion handler pattern with default `URLSession`, and marry that with the techniques outlined in [Extending Your App&#39;s Background Execution Time][3]. Now, that only buys you 3 minutes or so, but often that‚Äôs all we need. But if you think it may take more than three minutes to finish the uploads, then you‚Äôll need background `URLSessionConfiguration`.


